node.text:
Here's a close-up look of Celeste Lecaroz's "Tahip 2" 

The wind moves on her head covering that seems to fly. This dynamic painting is held in place by the somnolence of the carabao on the right: dignified and quiet in its repose. 

–Danton Remoto 

RÉPÉTITIO LECAROZ runs from June 30 until July 28, 2021. 

For appointments and other inquiries, you can send us a DM, text us at +63 917 560 0880, or email us at operations1335mabini@gmail.com

Can't view the show in person? Tap the link in our bio for the virtual tour. 

#1335mabini #artph #contemporaryart #celestelecaroz

node.text:
Pocket, a series of 4 x 4 inch paintings, serves as small ‘pockets’ of nature that are charged by the joy and purity nature brings, as well as the hope Caces wants to extend to his audience. It is a reminder to trust and hold on to the good amidst all adversities, be it big or small, in order for one to come out of situations with no regrets. Caces envisions that this collection, albeit small in size, can instill hope to everyone who comes across it.

Lee Caces (b. 1991)
Pocket (1-9)
2021
Mixed media on canvas
10.1 x 10.1 cm (4 x 4 in)

@artfairph #artfairph #artph #contemporaryart

node.text:
Joseph Tecson's solo show, 'Out of Coverage Areas' for Art Fair Philippines 2021 runs from May 6 to May 15, 2021 at 1335Mabini.

'Out of Coverage Areas' presents the notion to viewers that to escape and to disconnect is ultimately inherent when it comes to reconnecting with the world. Joseph Tecson’s days of painting in Rizal serves as a reminder to take the time to think, understand nature and its intricacies, and to be one with the deepest recesses of our being in order for us to be the most human versions of ourselves, especially within the context of today’s time.

Ultimately, 'Out of Coverage Areas' is a representation of will, an encapsulation of a breath, and an invitation to be alive and to keep on living.

To schedule an appointment and for other inquiries, you may reach out to us via operations1335mabini@gmail.com
—
www.the1335mabini.ph

View their works that explore nature and humanity in a time of isolation in person on May 6 to May 15, 2021 at 1335Mabini C1B Karrivin Plaza 2316 Chino Roces Avenue Extension, Makati City. Visits are limited and strictly by appointment only for everyone's safety.

To schedule an appointment and for other inquiries, you may reach out to us via operations1335mabini@gmail.com

—
www.the1335mabini.ph

node.text:
“In all chaos, there is a cosmos, in all disorder, a secret order”. – Carl Jung

In an age when life has become so uncertain, the world is given an alternate relationship with space and time. But in the middle of this unified experience of strangeness and loss, 0270501’s Rescheduled Mindfulness serves as a conscious observation and acceptance of what is.

Come and visit their works at 1335/MABINI, Karrivin Plaza, Chino Roces Ave. Extension, Makati. 

In association with Art Fair Philippines 2022. Reconsidering the Present runs until tomorrow, April 1.

node.text:
A sea of petals float atop a sea of darkness... 

Through the Solace in Shadows series, Filipina-Chinese artist Melissa Yeung-Yap wants to veer away from the superstitions that have surrounded shadows since time
immemorial, and in the process, shine a light on dying crafts in the Philippines that have long been left in the dark.

Come and visit her works at 1335/MABINI, Karrivin Plaza, Chino Roces Ave. Extension, Makati.

In association with Art Fair Philippines 2022, Reconsidering the Present runs until April 1 (Friday).

The lines between abstract and real blur in this collection by Cebuana sisters Julia & Jheane.

With local resources being used to depict foreign subjects— Paperweight shines a light on the Filipino cultural identity by showing the foreign influences that have contributed to it.

Come and visit their works at 1335/MABINI, Karrivin Plaza, Chino Roces Ave. Extension, Makati.

In association with Art Fair Philippines 2022, Reconsidering the Present runs until April 1 (Friday).

In association with Art Fair Philippines 2022, 1335/MABINI proudly presents: Reconsidering the Present, a series of three distinct exhibitions—all focusing on the interconnectedness of the local and the international, shining a light on how art can both stir and steer society towards a more connected future. 

Our featured artists include:
Julia & Jheane
Melissa Yeung-Yap
0270501

For inquiries and appointments, send us a DM or email us at inquire@1335mabini.info. Walk-ins are also allowed. 

Reconsidering the Present runs from March 23 to April 1, 2022.

We would also like to thank our talented artists @julia_alexis_b, @katrinajheane, @melissayeungyap, and @027.05.01, our beloved curator @no_not_ricardo, and all our wonderful guests and visitors. 

1335/MABINI's Reconsidering the Present runs from March 23-April 1, 2022.
